Today is our updated USDA inspection for the monkeys and rescue work… BIG day for the updated licensing…. More than 100 pages of veterinary care plans, nutrition planning, enrichment outlines, habitat planning, sanitary maintenance, contingency planning, and species outlines…. Not to mention enclosure expansions, updates, and new security installation… along with 60+ pages of updates to our IRS 501c3 and the future of the foundation… today is a BIG day… and yes I’m a nervous wreck!!!! 🤪😬
And we officially passed… we are licensed!!!!! Thanks @usdagov for standing behind us and our work!

Not going to lie… the last 2 weeks have been horrendous and awful. Stress at home due to direct attacks on my family, death threats, threats against my animals, impacts to my 501c3, loss of income, hateful messages, harassment, and lies… if it weren’t for my animals, my husband, my gym time and a small sense of hope… I don’t know where I’d be today! I’m tired… worn, and mostly just sad!

Sending DHS, CPS, Animal Control, and USDA here constantly puts the animals and my children at risk. They’re endangering the animals. And animal control will euthanize them if they continue to get calls. They’re trying to kill Winston… and have my kids taken away… and I’m done! Period. It’s unreal…
Here’s to a great Saturday and amazing weekend!

We would love to have you join us in this push to serve one of our dear friends and partners in rescue. The @carefoundationflorida in Florida, one of the best sanctuaries in the country, has some immediate needs, including an $1,800 emergency vet bill. The work of rescue is not easy and is never without a great cost. There is a need for $650 as well for helping handle excess utilities, and so much more right now. You can help serve Chimera the Liliger, Katrina the Tiger, Bubbles the Spider Monkey, Rosie the Capuchin, and Jamie the Fox right now. There is a link at the top of of my linktree where you can give directly to the Amazing team at Care Foundation. Thanks for helping save the animals and make an impact on the world. It means the world to me when you guys are generous to our friends.

⚠️⚠️Caution Graphic: 

The haters who love to stalk my posts, then lie all over on Reddit… when you claim I kicked a monkey… after having my arm torn open in .005 secs, he latched to my ankle, I shook him off… wanted you to see what real monkey life is with adult hormonal rehomes… it’s HARD AF!

97.5% of the time Mojo is laid back and sweet… and he is awesome. But he is a mature Vervet monkey that’s isn’t neutered… he’s been rehomed in the last 5 weeks. It’s traumatic, and he’s trying to sort who is alpha… working with and living with Monkeys means you will be bitten!

Thanks to your lies, drama, and petty game playing… we have had the authorities come inspect many times… but they find our work and the behavior and care of the animals to be more than exceptional… I am proud. Top quality enclosures, diet, care enrichment and lots of love!

So Haters, Liars and Drama addicts… keep spreading your lies… especially those who have no clue what it means to care for primates… you keep calling our care subpar, bad, etc… but none of you have the balls to take the bites, do the work, spend the time or the money to take on animals that are hard, dangerous and often Mia understood. 

You do you… Mean while… we will keep doing what we do… with pride, authenticity, care, focus, and accountability of a great community of Monkey friends, rescue and heroes. 

I’ll take the bites, ensure the hard stuff, and keep going because I love what I do, and I love these animals more than anyone understands!
Such a sweet, tiny little baby girl! 💜💜💜

Take a moment, consider being a life saver, a hero and a friend to one of the family… one of our amazing family of rescues and sanctuaries in Florida @carefoundationflorida …. their team is incredible, their passion is amazing, and their impact is crucial!
